name: Altamaha WMA—Waterfowl Management Area

seasons.details:
Butler Island opens after the last Saturday of waterfowl season.
Aug. 15-Nov. 15, Feb. 1- Feb. 28. No furbearer season.
Daily bag Limit: 6/person. C Archery Only, Butler Refuge Area: Jan. 17-18.

Shooting hours end at noon, except last day of season when shooting hours end at sunset.
Rhett’s Island: Wed., Sat., Sun., & State Holidays during statewide season.
Q20 Butler Island: Saturday only; see Quota Hunts.
Q20 Champney Island: Saturday & Sunday Only; see Quota Hunts. First hunt open only to youth and veterans to apply (other 2 party members don’t have to be youth or veteran). No stand-by hunters allowed. Max. 3 persons per quota party.
Mar. 1-May 31. Small game weapons only. Feral hogs may be hunted with dogs.

notes: Area includes Broughton, Butler, Champney, and Rhetts Islands.

Butler Refuge (east of Hwy 17 on Butler Island) and Ansley Hodges MARSH Project (west of Hwy 17 on Champney Island) are always closed to firearms but archery equipment may be used during open dates listed above to take deer, hog, and rabbits after the last Saturday of waterfowl season. Airboats are banned in managed waterfowl impoundments. Access to Rhetts Island is limited to designated crossover sites, with boats restricted to a 25hp motor or less. Fishing, shrimping, and crabbing are prohibited on Rhetts Island during early teal and statewide waterfowl season. Butler Island ponds and impoundments west of HWY 17 are closed to cast netting. Drone use, including launching and landing, is prohibited.
directions: From Darien: Take U.S. HWY 17 south 1.5 miles; check station is on the right.
